  "analyst_note": "SA44101: Pulse Secure advisory covering CVE-2019-11510 (arbitrary file read), CVE-2019-11508 (heap overflow in NFS), and CVE-2019-11538 (arbitrary file write). The /dana-na/ directory and DSID cookie are definitive Pulse Secure indicators. CVE-2019-11510 allows reading /etc/passwd and session files with cleartext VPN credentials \u2014 NSA alert AA20-010A confirms active nation-state exploitation. If Pulse Secure is detected, treat as critical \u2014 apply patches or isolate immediately.",
